  "prompt": "What are the aptitude questions asked in aryaka networks?",
  "response": "Aryaka Networks, like many tech companies, evaluates candidates through a combination of technical and aptitude assessments during their hiring process. While the exact questions may vary, here are some common types of aptitude questions you might encounter:\n\n### **1. Logical Reasoning**\n   - **Number Series**: Identify the pattern and find the missing number.  \n     E.g., 2, 4, 8, 16, ?  \n   - **Letter Series**: Find the next letter in the sequence.  \n     E.g., A, C, E, G, ?  \n   - **Logical Puzzles**: Solve puzzles involving arrangements, deductions, or analogies.  \n     E.g., \"If all Bloops are Razzies and all Razzies are Lazzies, are all Bloops definitely Lazzies?\"  \n\n### **2. Quantitative Aptitude**\n   - **Basic Arithmetic**: Questions on percentages, ratios, and averages.  \n     E.g., \"If the price of a product increases by 20%, by what percentage should the consumption decrease to keep the expenditure the same?\"  \n   - **Algebra**: Simple equations and word problems.  \n   - **Time and Work**: Problems involving efficiency and collaboration.  \n     E.g., \"A can complete a task in 10 days, and B can do it in 15 days. How long will they take together?\"  \n\n### **3. Verbal Ability**\n   - **Reading Comprehension**: Read a passage and answer questions based on it.  \n   - **Synonyms and Antonyms**: Identify words with similar or opposite meanings.  \n   - **Sentence Correction**: Spot and correct grammatical errors.  \n\n### **4. Technical Aptitude (if relevant)**\n   - **Networking Basics**: Questions on OSI model, TCP/IP, DNS, etc.  \n   - **Programming**: Simple coding problems or logic-based questions.  \n   - **Cloud and Security**: Basic concepts of cloud computing and cybersecurity.  \n\n### **5. Problem-Solving and Critical Thinking**\n   - Real-world scenarios to assess your ability to analyze and solve problems.  \n     E.g., \"How would you optimize network performance for a global company?\"  \n\n### **Tips for Preparation**\n- **Practice Aptitude Tests**: Use platforms like HackerRank, LeetCode, or AptitudePrep to practice questions.  \n- **Brush Up Basics**: Revise fundamental concepts in networking, mathematics, and logical reasoning.  \n- **Time Management**: Practice solving questions under time constraints.  \n\nIf you\u2019re applying for a specific role, focus on the relevant technical skills and concepts that align with the job description. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
